title: NASA Debunks Media Rumors on ISS Astronauts’ Health
text:
NASA has dismissed recent media claims about the health of astronauts Sunita "Suni" Williams and Butch Wilmore aboard the International Space Station (ISS).
Contrary to reports suggesting significant weight loss and health concerns, the space agency has assured the public that both astronauts are in excellent condition.
NASA Confirms ISS Astronauts in Good Health Amid Rumors
Dr. J.D. Polk, NASA's chief health and medical officer, emphasized that Williams and Wilmore are maintaining their pre-flight weight and continue to thrive in the microgravity environment, [Space](https://www.space.com/space-exploration/missions/all-astronauts-still-in-good-health-on-iss-nasa-flight-surgeon-says-amid-new-tabloid-rumors) said.
"Both astronauts weigh the same as when they launched," he said, explaining that changes in appearance, such as facial puffiness or muscle shifts, are common in space due to fluid redistribution and rigorous exercise routines.
The rumors originated from photos of Williams that some outlets described as showing her looking "gaunt." These speculations were fueled by comments from outside medical experts who suggested her appearance might indicate stress from the extended time in space.
Williams addressed the claims directly during a live interview from the ISS, stating, "I'm the same weight that I was when I got up here." She explained that her exercise regimen, which includes weightlifting and cycling, has slightly altered her physique, giving her a stronger build.
Polk further explained NASA's comprehensive approach to astronaut health. Crewmembers undergo daily exercise, weekly private medical checkups, and constant monitoring of their diet and overall well-being.
The astronauts also have access to an Internet Protocol (IP) phone to contact medical staff whenever needed. Polk reiterated that NASA has never had to return an astronaut early for medical reasons in the history of human spaceflight.

[Congress to Hear Testimony on UFOs as Controversial Claims of DoD Disinformation Surface](/articles/51597/20241114/congress-hear-testimony-ufos-controversial-claims-dod-disinformation-surface.htm)
Starliner Delays Extend ISS Stay, But NASA Assures Astronauts Are Thriving
Wilmore, who launched to the ISS with Williams in June aboard Boeing's Starliner spacecraft, has also been the subject of similar rumors.
According to [Gizmodo](https://gizmodo.com/nasa-astronaut-suni-williams-shouldnt-have-to-discuss-her-weight-to-dismiss-tabloid-rumors-2000524132), media outlets suggested he might have experienced weight loss during the extended mission. However, NASA clarified that Wilmore, like Williams, is in excellent health.
The astronauts' mission was initially scheduled to last only 10 days, but technical issues with Starliner extended their stay to eight months. Despite the unexpected change, NASA confirmed that the ISS has ample supplies to support the crew until their scheduled return in February 2025 aboard SpaceX's Crew Dragon.
This situation highlights the challenges astronauts face not only in space but also in dealing with public scrutiny. Williams' and Wilmore's professionalism and fitness demonstrate their preparedness to handle the demands of prolonged missions. NASA remains committed to ensuring their health and safety throughout their time aboard the ISS.

title: Limpiar Unveils On-Demand App Offering Same-Day, Last-Minute, Eco-Friendly Cleaning to Dallas Homes | User | mammothtimes.com
text:
On a mission to provide a convenient and environmentally conscious cleaning solution, Limpiar is poised to become the go-to choice for individuals seeking same-day, last-minute; on-demand cleaning services in the Dallas-Fort Worth metroplex.
Between hectic work schedules, children's activities, and a never-ending list of errands, maintaining a clean home often takes a backseat for many Dallas residents. Recognizing this challenge, Limpiar , a game-changing on-demand cleaning app and manufacturer of eco-friendly cleaning products, is set to transform how Dallasites approach house cleaning.
Limpiar's mobile app connects users with vetted, professional cleaners who employ Limpiar's line of gentle, sustainable products to deliver same day last-minute and same-day cleaning services for homes, offices, and short-term rentals.
Limpiar distinguishes itself through its commitment to quality and sustainability. Key features that set Limpiar apart include meticulous vetting and training of cleaners, on-demand booking options, the use of eco-friendly and pet-friendly products, transparent pricing, and a community-focused approach.
Demi Oloyede, co-founder and CEO of Limpiar, emphasizes the company's commitment to delivering a premium and fast cleaning service . Oleyede Oloyede said: "Limpiar is not just a cleaning service; it's a commitment to providing quick, efficient, and eco-friendly cleaning solutions. I'm excited about this pivotal step in using Limpiar to redefine the cleaning experience."
Limpiar's dedication to sustainability is reflected in its use of green-certified cleaning products. Oloyede said the company believes in treating every home and furry family member with care. Limpiar exclusively uses products that are safe for people, pets, and the environment.
Transparent pricing and community commitment
Limpiar prides itself on transparent pricing, ensuring that families see the cost of their cleaning service upfront, eliminating hidden fees. The secure payment system through the app adds an extra layer of convenience for users.
Jake Adebayo, Chief Technology Officer at Limpiar, said as co-founder at SkillPatron, he witnessed the transformative power of technology in connecting skilled professionals with business opportunities. He added: "Now, atLimpiar, we're leveraging that experience to reimagine the cleaning industry."
In addition to providing top-notch green cleaning services, Limpiar is committed to giving back to the community. The company has sealed partnerships with local animal shelters and environmental organizations, donating cleaning supplies and volunteering time to enhance the cleanliness of the community.
5-star ratings from Dallasites
So far, Limpiar has earned top ratings from Dallasites, making it a game-changing app and a must-have in the community for 2024.
Lisset Velando, Vice President of Silvus, Inc., said she had already used Limpiar twice now for her Uptown Dallas apartment.
"Both times, my Limpiadors have done a fantastic job. They arrived on time, cleaned thoroughly, handled linen changes, and were always respectful and polite. I'll be using Limpiar again for future cleanings. Plus, communicating and booking with them is a breeze," shared Lisset.
Blair Hendrix, the owner of Smatch North Texas, described Limpiar as a "savior" after a busy week.
"Today's Tidy experience was rough, but who cares? I'm raving about Kandi from Limpiar! She and her crew saved the day with a last-minute appointment, going above and beyond. They even removed toilet lids and sink handles! If you need cleaning help, Limpiar is the way to go," shared Blair.
Limpiar, currently in beta testing, invites passionate and reliable cleaners to join its team in the DFW metro. Those interested in delivering sparkling clean homes can apply through the Limpiar onboarding portal: https://limpiar.online/become-a-limpiador . Residents eager to experience Limpiar's convenience and quality can download the app from the App Store or Google Play and sign up for the beta waitlist: https://limpiar.online/waitlist/ .
Demi Oloyede expresses enthusiasm for the beta phase, stating, "During our beta phase, Limpiar users can seamlessly connect to local cleaning opportunities for free, making earning through cleaning more accessible than ever. We're not just launching a platform; we're creating a community that empowers every cleaner."
About Limpiar
Limpiar is a cutting-edge, on-demand cleaning service that provides quick and efficient cleaning solutions. With a focus on eco-friendliness, pet-friendliness, and convenience, Limpiar is poised to become the go-to choice for individuals seeking on-demand cleaning services. author: João Gabriel
title: Não é só Need for Speed - EA vai desligar quatro jogos em outubro
text:
Outubro é o famoso “mês das bruxas” e, para quem curte jogos de esportes da EA, vai ser um período realmente assustador. A produtora vai “matar” um total de quatro games ao longo do mês, desligando seus servidores e removendo os títulos de suas plataformas online.
No mês passado já tivemos notícia de Need for Speed: Rivals acelerando para fora do catálogo da EA no mês de outubro. Não só isso, mas há rumores de que a série pode ter sido encerrada de vez.
Foto: Divulgação/EA Mas o título não vai embora sozinho. No mesmo mês teremos também o encerramento de FIFA 23, do título de hockey NHL 21 e do jogo de futebol americano Madden NFL 22. A lista completa, com suas datas de desligamento, é a seguinte:
NHL 21 encerra no dia 6 de outubro Need for Speed: Rivals encerra no 7 de outubro Madden NFL 22 encerra no dia 20 de outubro FIFA 23 encerra no dia 30 de outubro Divulgação/Electronic Arts Os três primeiros jogos já aparecem na página oficial de encerramento de suporte da EA. Já FIFA 23 deveria durar ainda até dezembro, mas o site GameBlog afirma que a produtora antecipou seu funeral para a véspera do Halloween.
EA não pretende parar de “matar” jogos É normal o encerramento de suporte a jogos por parte de grandes produtoras como a EA, prática que acontece continuamente ao longo de todo ano.
No entanto, “matar” quatro jogos de uma vez num único mês certamente deve chamar a atenção do movimento Stop Killing Games , que tem conquistado tração na Europa.
Leia mais:
Tendo a polêmica de The Crew como seu principal ponto de partida, a petição visa pressionar autoridades no velho continente a criar garantias de que grandes produtoras tenham algum compromisso em manter seus títulos jogáveis depois que já não querem mais trabalhar com eles.
No entanto, até que o movimento tenha algum resultado concreto (se tiver), ainda veremos muitos outros games sendo enterrados.
